have made such an impression
on you.

33:45.960 --> 33:50.000
- Why do you keep saying that?
- You mean I'm mistaken?

33:50.040 --> 33:52.480
All right.

33:52.520 --> 33:55.560
Let it go.
Leave me with my memories.

33:55.600 --> 34:00.440
If it in some way helps you get
it off your chest or something...

34:00.480 --> 34:02.960
What a compassionate fellow
you are, Nigel.

34:03.000 --> 34:05.440
Actually, to tell the truth,
I should be going.

34:05.480 --> 34:08.320
My wife will think
I've fallen overboard.

34:08.360 --> 34:10.719
You'd have made
a very good analyst.

34:10.760 --> 34:14.080
Not many men would have listened
to so much for so long.

34:16.040 --> 34:17.920
Well, anyway,
thanks for the drink.

35:08.840 --> 35:11.560
I can't understand why he'd
think you'd be interested...

35:11.600 --> 35:13.000
in all these sordid details.

35:13.040 --> 35:14.120
I haven't a clue.

35:14.160 --> 35:15.240
Probably lets his hair down...

35:15.280 --> 35:17.560
every time he corners
a captive audience, poor chap.

35:17.600 --> 35:20.680
Poor chap.
He's a verbal exhibitionist.

35:20.720 --> 35:22.600
It's his wife I feel sorry for.

35:22.640 --> 35:25.480
Yeah. Did I mention I met her
in the bar last night?

35:25.520 --> 35:27.640
- No.
- No, I didn't, did I?

35:27.680 --> 35:30.600
- Was she feeling better?
- Yeah, much better.

35:30.640 --> 35:33.040
She's not bad-Iooking, actually.

35:35.600 --> 35:36.800
Thank you.

35:36.840 --> 35:37.960
They're coming.

35:38.000 --> 35:39.240
What?

35:39.280 --> 35:41.280
Your American friend
and his wife.

35:44.560 --> 35:47.200
God. Just as long as he
doesn't park himself on us.

35:47.240 --> 35:48.560
After what he
told you last night?

35:48.600 --> 35:49.840
He wouldn't dare, would he?

35:49.880 --> 35:52.840
Nigel, old chap.
Good to see you.

35:52.880 --> 35:55.000
This must be
your lovely wife.

35:55.040 --> 35:58.080
Hi there, I'm Oscar. Mimi
you already know, don't you?

35:59.720 --> 36:01.320
So do you, Nigel, right?

36:02.480 --> 36:04.000
I hate to break up a twosome...

36:04.080 --> 36:05.640
but would you mind
if I joined you?

36:05.680 --> 36:08.040
We had an invitation
to the Captain's table.

36:08.080 --> 36:09.880
Trouble is,
I'm allergic to beards.

36:09.920 --> 36:11.720
Are you allergic to cripples?

36:13.280 --> 36:15.480
After an intro like that,
how can we refuse?

36:15.520 --> 36:16.920
Fine. It's settled, then.

36:16.960 --> 36:18.360
Off you go, baby.

36:18.400 --> 36:21.200
Thanks. Have fun.

36:21.240 --> 36:23.800
Mimi doesn't share my aversion.

36:23.840 --> 36:26.680
In fact,
she's not too choosy in general.

36:26.720 --> 36:28.960
Can't be, or she couldn't
have married me.

36:30.960 --> 36:33.640
What a girl.

36:33.680 --> 36:35.480
Knockin' 'em dead as usual.

36:35.520 --> 36:37.400
Just wine for me. White.

36:37.440 --> 36:40.880
Anything,
as long as it's not retsina.

36:40.920 --> 36:43.680
Yes, Mimi's very lovely,
but you...

36:43.720 --> 36:45.440
I still don't know your name,
by the way.

36:45.480 --> 36:46.560
Fiona.

36:46.600 --> 36:48.920
Fiona. I hope you won't
think me forward...

36:48.960 --> 36:51.920
but I find your own brand
of beauty more subtle.

36:51.960 --> 36:53.800
It has that inimitably
British quality...

36:53.840 --> 36:57.560
a kind of reticence that hints
at untapped potentiality.

36:57.600 --> 37:01.080
Nigel's been tapping
my potentialities for years...

37:01.120 --> 37:02.360
haven't you, Nigel?

37:02.400 --> 37:03.760
Well, Nigel?

37:05.280 --> 37:07.880
Come on, your lovely wife
has just implied...

37:07.920 --> 37:10.160
that she's lost
all her mystery for you.

37:10.200 --> 37:11.680
True or false?

37:11.720 --> 37:13.800
I think there's probably
a corner of everyone...

37:13.840 --> 37:14.960
that remains to be explored.

37:16.920 --> 37:20.040
Halfhearted,
but better than nothing.

37:20.080 --> 37:22.480
Well, Fiona, they'll
have to make do with that.

37:22.520 --> 37:26.240
He's right, though. Everyone
has secret nooks and crannies.

37:26.280 --> 37:28.200
Every relationship,
no matter how harmonious...

37:28.240 --> 37:31.120
contains seeds of farce
or tragedy.

37:38.120 --> 37:39.720
I do not like
the look of that sky.

37:39.760 --> 37:41.040
I'm not sure if the weather's
going to hold.

37:41.080 --> 37:43.840
Jesus, don't tell me you're
taking refuge in the weather.

37:43.880 --> 37:45.280
You know what I hope?

37:45.320 --> 37:46.680
I hope the ship goes down...

37:46.720 --> 37:48.640
and we're all marooned
on a desert island.

37:48.720 --> 37:50.160
I'd wind up
the sole survivor.

37:50.200 --> 37:52.160
That's charming.
And why do you say that?

37:52.240 --> 37:53.800
Because
no one would be tempted...

37:53.840 --> 37:56.040
to cannibalize
my shriveled carcass.

38:14.160 --> 38:16.360
I hope he hasn't
been boring you.

38:16.400 --> 38:17.840
No, not at all.

38:17.840 --> 38:19.520
Your husband
has a great sense of humor.

38:19.560 --> 38:21.960
Black humor, but still,
he's been keeping us...

38:22.000 --> 38:22.960
thoroughly entertained.

38:22.960 --> 38:24.880
- See, baby?
- See what?

38:24.880 --> 38:26.600
Our British friends
find me entertaining.

38:26.640 --> 38:28.720
In small doses, perhaps.

38:28.760 --> 38:31.360
But now we must leave them
in peace.

38:31.400 --> 38:33.560
Ah. Indeed.

38:33.600 --> 38:35.400
Thanks for taking care of him.

38:35.440 --> 38:37.320
Not at all.

38:37.360 --> 38:40.520
Ah, Fiona, I've already
imposed on you...

38:40.560 --> 38:42.400
but may I beg a favor?

38:42.440 --> 38:43.760
As I'm sure he told you...

38:43.800 --> 38:45.800
Nigel and I
had a chat last night.

38:45.840 --> 38:48.680
I found him
such stimulating company.

38:48.720 --> 38:50.800
Could I borrow him again
this afternoon?

38:50.840 --> 38:52.520
Just for an hour or so.

38:52.560 --> 38:55.080
He's quite grown up. He doesn't
have to have Mummy's permission.

39:07.080 --> 39:08.960
The seasons came and went.

39:09.000 --> 39:12.680
Mimi's face still held
a thousand mysteries for me...

39:12.720 --> 39:16.160
her body
a thousand sweet promises.

39:16.200 --> 39:18.120
But lurking
at the back of my mind...

39:18.160 --> 39:21.120
was an unspoken fear that we'd
already scaled the heights...

39:21.200 --> 39:22.880
of our relationship...

39:22.920 --> 39:25.760
that it would all be downhill
from now on.

39:25.800 --> 39:27.680
And then something happened.

39:29.480 --> 39:33.200
Something that would put things
on a totally different plane.

39:35.400 --> 39:39.080
We were at Kitzbuhel,
a skiing vacation.

39:39.120 --> 39:41.040
I'd rented a chalet there.

39:41.040 --> 39:43.280
It was one of those nights...

39:43.320 --> 39:45.720
warm and cozy inside...

39:45.760 --> 39:47.880
great, fat snowflakes...

39:47.920 --> 39:51.680
drifting down in the blackness
beyond the frosted panes.

39:51.720 --> 39:55.040
No light but the glow
from the set.

39:55.080 --> 39:57.760
Mimi on the floor wearing
a T-shirt and nothing else...

39:57.800 --> 40:02.080
watching some old American soap
dubbed in German...

40:02.160 --> 40:04.480
and me on the couch
watching her...

40:04.520 --> 40:07.360
sprawled in a sort
of boozy stupor.

40:07.400 --> 40:09.280
All at once she got up...

40:11.080 --> 40:13.800
stalked over to the set...

40:13.840 --> 40:16.520
spread her legs...

40:16.560 --> 40:18.560
and pissed on the screen...

40:18.600 --> 40:21.360
like she wanted to blot it out.

40:21.400 --> 40:25.360
Time stood still for an instant,
and then I rolled off the couch.

40:25.400 --> 40:27.440
I crawled over like a lunatic.

40:27.480 --> 40:29.760
I wormed my way
between her legs...

40:29.800 --> 40:31.640
and I turned over.

40:31.680 --> 40:32.800
And right away...

40:32.840 --> 40:38.120
I was engulfed with this warm,
golden cascade.

40:38.160 --> 40:40.480
It spattered my cheeks...

40:40.520 --> 40:43.280
it filled my nostrils,
it stung my eyes...

40:43.320 --> 40:46.320
and then something
jolted my brain...

40:46.360 --> 40:49.480
with multi-megavolt intensity.

40:49.520 --> 40:54.160
There was this blinding flash
in the back of my eyeballs.

40:54.200 --> 40:57.120
I experienced
the orgasm of a lifetime.

40:57.160 --> 40:59.080
For God's sake, man!

40:59.120 --> 41:02.520
It was like a white-hot blade
piercing me through and through.

41:02.560 --> 41:05.400
This was my Nile,
my Ganges, my Jordan...

41:05.440 --> 41:07.600
my Fountain of Youth,
my second baptism.

41:07.640 --> 41:09.960
I think I'm probably
as broad-minded...

41:10.000 --> 41:12.520
as the next man...
but, I mean, obviously...

41:12.560 --> 41:13.600
there are limits.

41:13.640 --> 41:15.040
Stop twittering, Nigel.

41:15.120 --> 41:18.400
I'm sharing a revelation
with you, damn it.

41:18.480 --> 41:20.800
I'm trying to expand
your sexual horizons.

41:20.840 --> 41:22.800
I see. And what makes you
think they need expanding?

41:22.840 --> 41:27.080
