41:40.480 --> 41:41.840
It's just downright obscene.

41:41.880 --> 41:43.000
Obscene?

41:43.040 --> 41:46.280
Have you ever felt real,
overpowering passion?

41:46.320 --> 41:48.960
Have you ever truly
idolized a woman?

41:49.000 --> 41:51.560
Nothing can be obscene
in such a love.

41:51.560 --> 41:53.600
Everything that occurs
between you...

41:53.640 --> 41:55.840
becomes a sacrament,
don't you see?

41:57.840 --> 41:59.160
Come on. Sit down.

41:59.200 --> 42:01.480
Have another cup of tea.

42:01.520 --> 42:03.080
It'll steady your nerves.

42:05.920 --> 42:09.280
So, anyway...

42:09.360 --> 42:12.040
that was our sexual Rubicon.

42:12.080 --> 42:15.520
It opened up all sorts
of new possibilities.

42:54.880 --> 42:57.000
I always had a suspicion...

42:57.040 --> 42:59.080
it might be
supremely pleasurable...

42:59.120 --> 43:03.400
to be humiliated
by a beautiful woman...

43:03.440 --> 43:06.520
but it was only now
I realized...

43:06.560 --> 43:08.680
what this could entail.

45:10.040 --> 45:14.160
We shut ourselves up with
our toys for weeks on end...

45:14.200 --> 45:15.760
never going out...

45:15.800 --> 45:18.440
seeing no one but each other.

45:18.480 --> 45:21.520
I guess it was asking
too much of any couple.

45:21.560 --> 45:22.680
Oscar?

45:22.720 --> 45:23.880
Just a minute.

45:25.040 --> 45:27.640
Did you really have
all those women?

45:27.680 --> 45:29.200
What women?

45:29.240 --> 45:31.200
The ones you write about.

45:33.560 --> 45:34.960
Does it matter?

45:35.000 --> 45:36.880
It's a book, for Christ's sake.

45:36.920 --> 45:38.320
I know. I'm just curious.

45:38.360 --> 45:41.200
Do you like it?
That's what matters.

45:41.240 --> 45:43.040
It's very sexy.

45:43.080 --> 45:45.960
Forget about sex
for two seconds.

45:46.000 --> 45:48.280
What do you think of the quality
of the writing?

45:48.320 --> 45:51.240
I can't judge.
My English isn't good enough.

45:51.280 --> 45:53.160
"My English isn't good enough."

45:53.200 --> 45:55.080
Why read the fucking book
at all?

45:55.120 --> 45:56.520
Because I love you.

45:56.520 --> 45:59.000
Because I love everything
to do with you.

45:59.040 --> 46:01.320
It's a pity
you're not in publishing.

46:01.360 --> 46:04.640
I'd be at the top
of the best-seller list by now.

46:04.720 --> 46:06.800
When will it be published?

46:06.840 --> 46:08.200
You tell me.

46:09.320 --> 46:11.320
I'm working on it.

46:11.360 --> 46:14.920
We were getting to be
like two goldfish in a bowl.

46:14.960 --> 46:17.920
"Come on," I told her,
"We need a change of scene.

46:18.000 --> 46:20.840
"Let's each round up
a few friends and hit the town."

46:48.760 --> 46:52.880
You know it.
It's true. It's true.

48:03.120 --> 48:04.560
Hey, what's the matter?

48:09.440 --> 48:11.320
I'd always found infidelity...

48:11.360 --> 48:15.040
the most titillating aspect
of any relationship.

48:15.080 --> 48:18.280
That scene
should have turned me on.

48:18.320 --> 48:21.160
So why didn't it?

48:21.200 --> 48:23.320
Why did I feel so hurt?

48:25.160 --> 48:27.600
Pas de cigarette,
s'il vous plait.

48:53.320 --> 48:55.360
Why did you do it?

48:59.440 --> 49:02.040
Why don't you say something?

49:02.080 --> 49:03.520
What do you want me to say?

49:03.560 --> 49:06.440
Why did you walk out on me
like that?

49:06.480 --> 49:07.880
You don't know?

49:07.920 --> 49:09.640
Well, you started it.

49:09.680 --> 49:12.080
Flirting with my own roommate.

49:12.120 --> 49:13.680
You were all over her.

49:13.720 --> 49:15.880
Bullshit. We were having
a couple laughs.

49:15.920 --> 49:17.320
And we were just having a dance.

49:17.360 --> 49:21.320
Some dance. Decent of you
not to fuck him on the floor.

49:21.360 --> 49:24.520
I'm sorry.
I did it because I was jealous.

49:24.520 --> 49:26.600
Please, please forgive me.

49:26.640 --> 49:28.040
You're my Tiger.

49:28.080 --> 49:30.760
I don't want anyone but you...

49:30.800 --> 49:32.520
not ever.

49:32.560 --> 49:36.240
I love you. I love you.

49:36.280 --> 49:40.600
I loved her, too,
but our credit was running out.

49:40.640 --> 49:43.320
We were headed
for sexual bankruptcy.

49:56.080 --> 49:58.440
I smell pig.

50:02.600 --> 50:03.680
Don't laugh.

50:03.720 --> 50:05.200
Don't talk.

50:05.240 --> 50:07.880
Come, piggy.

50:07.920 --> 50:09.920
Where is he?

50:09.960 --> 50:12.320
Come, piggy-wiggy.

50:13.840 --> 50:15.680
Where are you?

50:27.880 --> 50:30.120
Get off. Get off.

50:31.400 --> 50:35.560
How dare you try to fuck me,
you filthy beast!

50:35.600 --> 50:36.680
Take that.

50:42.520 --> 50:43.760
Harder.

50:43.800 --> 50:44.920
Shut up.

50:47.160 --> 50:49.720
Oh, you spoiled it.

50:51.000 --> 50:52.400
Pigs don't talk.

50:52.440 --> 50:55.000
How can I believe
in a pig that talks?

51:00.280 --> 51:01.720
You know something?

51:03.480 --> 51:05.880
I don't believe in it, either.

51:07.320 --> 51:08.760
Not anymore.

51:17.360 --> 51:18.920
That was it.

51:18.960 --> 51:21.040
The spell was broken at last.

51:21.080 --> 51:23.720
Jolly good thing, too,
if you ask me.

51:23.760 --> 51:25.800
I dread to think
what you'd get up to next.

51:25.840 --> 51:29.200
Don't worry.
There's plenty more to tell.

51:29.240 --> 51:31.400
What makes you think
I want to hear it?

51:31.440 --> 51:33.480
I still don't know
what gives you the idea...

51:33.480 --> 51:35.400
that I enjoy being used
as a rubbish dump...

51:35.440 --> 51:36.680
for your unsavory reminiscences.

51:36.720 --> 51:38.880
Don't you?

51:38.920 --> 51:40.720
Don't you really, Nigel?

51:44.560 --> 51:46.120
He's still here?

51:46.160 --> 51:50.760
Afraid I am, yes,
but I'm just off now.

51:50.800 --> 51:55.080
You know, Nigel has been
extremely patient with me.

51:55.120 --> 51:58.800
We don't see eye-to-eye
on everything...

51:58.840 --> 52:01.960
but we share at least
one interest in common...

52:02.000 --> 52:03.360
you, baby.

52:03.400 --> 52:07.920
I suppose that's why he
keeps coming back for more.

52:07.960 --> 52:10.640
Anyway, as I say, I'm just off.

52:10.680 --> 52:12.920
So, thanks very much
for the tea.

52:12.960 --> 52:14.120
Toodle-oo.

52:33.120 --> 52:34.200
Oh. Sorry.

52:34.240 --> 52:35.960
You were gone long enough.

52:36.000 --> 52:37.400
I'm really sorry, darling.

52:37.440 --> 52:39.320
I was going to go to dinner
without you.

52:39.360 --> 52:41.080
It's just incredibly hard
to get away.

52:41.120 --> 52:42.760
You saw what he's like.

52:42.800 --> 52:45.680
- Was she there, too?
- Who?

52:45.720 --> 52:46.800
Wrong answer, Nigel.

52:46.840 --> 52:49.080
"Yes" or "no" would have
been fine, but "who?"

52:49.120 --> 52:51.040
You know perfectly well
who I mean.

52:51.080 --> 52:55.280
Right, Mimi. Yeah, she rolled up
just as I was leaving.

52:55.320 --> 52:56.440
Odd creature.

52:56.480 --> 52:59.000
So you said...
"Odd, but not bad-Iooking."

52:59.040 --> 53:00.440
Most men would find her
stunning.

53:00.480 --> 53:01.920
Most women, too,
for that matter.

53:01.960 --> 53:05.240
Well, look, I am not "most men."

53:05.280 --> 53:08.600
I'm your husband. Right?

53:08.640 --> 53:10.040
There we go.

53:10.080 --> 53:13.160
Here they are, all locked up.

53:13.200 --> 53:14.840
I say,
is this your little girl?

53:14.880 --> 53:17.240
It is, indeed. Amrita, say hello
to the lady and gentleman.

53:17.280 --> 53:18.680
Hello, Amrita.
That's a very pretty name.

53:18.720 --> 53:20.200
It's almost as pretty
as you are.

53:20.240 --> 53:23.000
She's enchanting.
Where have you been hiding her?

53:23.040 --> 53:24.920
I have a nanny
that looks after her.

53:24.960 --> 53:27.560
- And your wife?
- I'm a widower, dear lady.

53:27.600 --> 53:29.520
Oh, I'm so sorry.

53:29.520 --> 53:32.040
Anyway, it's lovely
to have a child on board.

53:32.080 --> 53:34.440
It makes a change
from all the wrinklies.

53:34.480 --> 53:37.320
And you? Have you provided
for your posterity?

53:37.360 --> 53:38.440
Sorry?

53:38.480 --> 53:40.280
You have a wife
that loves children so much.

53:40.320 --> 53:42.440
I was just wondering if
you yourself have a family.

53:42.480 --> 53:44.200
No, we haven't, actually.

53:44.240 --> 53:46.600
No. Nigel thinks the world's
overpopulated enough as it is...

53:46.640 --> 53:49.000
without us adding
to the problem.

53:49.040 --> 53:51.400
An admirable sentiment in India,
perhaps...

53:51.440 --> 53:53.360
But surely the green fields
of England...

53:53.400 --> 53:56.200
can afford to have
a few more mouths to feed.

53:56.240 --> 53:57.960
I say, look at that.

53:58.000 --> 53:59.400
Oh, look, Amrita, look. See.

53:59.440 --> 54:01.640
- Isn't that beautiful?
- Are you cold, darling?

54:01.680 --> 54:04.040
Gosh,
I should have brought my coat.

54:04.080 --> 54:06.280
Please, allow me.

54:06.320 --> 54:07.560
That's very kind.

54:07.600 --> 54:09.040
- Here we are.
- Thank you.

54:10.320 --> 54:12.560
Let's go and I'll fetch you
something from the cabin.

54:12.600 --> 54:14.200
See you in a sec.

54:15.880 --> 54:17.640
Believe me, dear lady...

54:17.640 --> 54:20.200
children are a better
form of marital therapy...

54:20.200 --> 54:21.800
than any trip to India.

54:34.280 --> 54:36.520
You mustn't believe all he says.

54:36.560 --> 54:38.440
He's a sick man.

54:38.480 --> 54:39.880
He imagines things.

54:44.200 --> 54:46.760
Please, don't think badly of me.

54:48.680 --> 54:50.000
Now, wait a minute.

54:50.040 --> 54:52.240
What are you playing at
this time?

54:52.280 --> 54:55.600
It matters to me what you think.

54:55.640 --> 54:56.840
Does it?

54:58.200 --> 54:59.600
Does it really?

54:59.640 --> 55:02.000
I have to talk with you, Nigel.

55:02.040 --> 55:04.040
I have to explain.

55:05.320 --> 55:07.560
All right, go ahead.

55:07.600 --> 55:09.000
No. Not here.

55:09.040 --> 55:10.440
In my cabin.

55:10.480 --> 55:13.480
We won't be disturbed there.

55:13.520 --> 55:14.640
Please.

55:14.680 --> 55:18.760
I'm afraid I can't. Not now.

55:18.800 --> 55:20.360
No. Later.

55:20.400 --> 55:22.400
Five o'clock.

55:22.440 --> 55:24.320
Cabin DS1.

55:36.760 --> 55:38.680
What is it?

55:41.560 --> 55:42.840
A newspaper.

55:43.960 --> 55:45.360
I brought your coat.

55:45.400 --> 55:46.800
Thanks, Mr. Singh.

55:46.840 --> 55:48.000
You're very welcome.

55:50.280 --> 55:52.400
- What a lovely story.
- Thanks.

55:52.440 --> 55:53.920
Say thank you, Amrita.

55:53.960 --> 55:55.600
So if your daddy will let me
I'll come and tell you...

55:55.640 --> 55:58.360
some other stories sometime.
Would you like that?

55:59.400 --> 56:01.200
Two hearts.

56:01.240 --> 56:03.000
I pass.

56:04.440 --> 56:06.000
Four hearts.

56:06.040 --> 56:07.440
Ich passe.

56:07.480 --> 56:08.560
No bid.

56:08.600 --> 56:09.720
Pass.

56:30.760 --> 56:32.200
You won't believe this...

56:32.240 --> 56:34.920
but I've got to see
that chap again.

56:34.920 --> 56:37.320
I thought you'd had enough
of all that.

56:37.360 --> 56:41.480
I know, it's just...
he won't take no for an answer.

56:41.520 --> 56:44.800
I'm so sorry,
but I've simply got to go.

56:44.880 --> 56:48.000
I wonder, would you like
to take my place?

56:48.040 --> 56:49.880
- I should be delighted.
- Great.

56:49.920 --> 56:51.720
Bridge is king of games.

56:51.720 --> 56:54.600
I once played
forty-eight hours nonstop.

56:54.640 --> 56:57.000
You leave your partner
in safe hands.

56:57.040 --> 56:58.440
Excellent.
I do apologize.

56:58.480 --> 56:59.880
Please, excuse me.

56:59.880 --> 57:01.800
Entschuldigung and all that.

57:37.560 --> 57:39.000
May I come in?

57:46.680 --> 57:48.520
Close the door.

58:11.000 --> 58:13.160
April Fool!

58:17.360 --> 58:19.680
You pathetic, sick...

58:22.520 --> 58:24.480
Do you want her?

58:24.560 --> 58:26.120
Yes or no.

58:26.160 --> 58:29.080
I don't want anything more to do
with either of you, ever.

58:29.120 --> 58:31.520
Let go.
Let me go, or I'Il...

58:31.560 --> 58:34.440
Let me go
or I'll call my mommy.

58:34.480 --> 58:36.840
Go on.

58:36.880 --> 58:38.600
Get out.

58:38.640 --> 58:41.360
Crawl back
to your matrimonial tomb.

58:47.280 --> 58:49.640
You know what? I pity you.

58:49.680 --> 58:51.560
I genuinely pity you both...

58:51.560 --> 58:53.880
if this is how
you get your kicks.

58:53.920 --> 58:56.320
I get no kicks out of this.

58:56.400 --> 58:58.200
Then what was this farce?

58:58.240 --> 59:00.640
How else could we get you here?

59:03.520 --> 59:06.840
Why is that suddenly
of such incredible importance?

59:06.880 --> 59:10.120
Mimi wants you to hear
the rest of our story.

59:10.160 --> 59:13.120
She thinks it'll help
her chances with you.

59:13.160 --> 59:15.240
What are you, her pimp?

59:15.280 --> 59:17.600
I don't begrudge Mimi
the right to look elsewhere...

59:17.640 --> 59:20.520
for what I can no longer supply.

59:20.560 --> 59:23.880
I merely supervise her affairs
instead of...

59:23.920 --> 59:25.320
submitting to them.

59:26.960 --> 59:29.160
You can have her, Nigel...

59:29.200 --> 59:30.600
with my blessings.

59:30.640 --> 59:33.320
On one condition...

59:33.320 --> 59:34.600
you hear me out.

59:39.760 --> 59:41.320
You make me sick.

59:41.360 --> 59:43.280
Why are you still standing here?

59:44.720 --> 59:48.000
Come on, Nigel, it was a joke.

59:48.040 --> 59:51.040
Have a sense of humor,
for Christ's sake.

59:51.080 --> 59:52.320
Come on, sit down.

59:52.360 --> 59:53.840
Make yourself comfortable.

59:53.880 --> 59:55.080
Use my wheelchair.

01:00:03.600 --> 01:00:05.600
The brake! The brake!

01:00:10.680 --> 01:00:12.520
Have a heart, Nigel.

01:00:16.360 --> 01:00:17.800
Don't be too rough...

01:00:17.800 --> 01:00:21.400
on a man demolished
by a love that was too strong.

01:00:27.400 --> 01:00:29.280
Yes, sir.

01:00:29.320 --> 01:00:31.640
We should have
stopped right there.

01:00:33.160 --> 01:00:37.560
Lovers should quit when
their passion is at its peak...

01:00:37.600 --> 01:00:40.800
not wait until
its inevitable decline.

01:00:46.800 --> 01:00:51.080
As it was, my desire for her
had begun to wane.

01:00:53.160 --> 01:00:54.760
There she would lie...

01:00:54.760 --> 01:00:57.840
gorgeous, voluptuous...

01:00:57.880 --> 01:01:00.760
and it didn't do a thing for me.

01:01:00.800 --> 01:01:03.560
I came to resent her failure
to excite me...

01:01:03.560 --> 01:01:05.160
the way she used to.

01:01:12.040 --> 01:01:16.480
We were developing a narcotic
dependence on television...

01:01:16.520 --> 01:01:20.120
the marital aid that enables
a couple to endure each other...

01:01:20.160 --> 01:01:22.400
without having to talk.

01:01:32.560 --> 01:01:35.440
A New York editress
was overnighting in Paris...

01:01:35.480 --> 01:01:37.440
on her way
to the Frankfurt book fair.

01:01:37.480 --> 01:01:39.960
I wanted to show her
a good time.

01:01:40.000 --> 01:01:41.560
It was a PR job...

01:01:41.600 --> 01:01:44.440
and I was apprehensive
of her reaction to Mimi...

01:01:44.480 --> 01:01:47.600
who tended to upstage
every other woman in sight.

01:01:47.640 --> 01:01:48.760
You wearing that?

01:01:49.760 --> 01:01:50.840
That dress?

01:01:50.880 --> 01:01:52.160
What about it?

01:01:54.000 --> 01:01:55.520
Couldn't you wear
something else?

01:01:58.240 --> 01:01:59.480
What's wrong with it?

01:01:59.520 --> 01:02:01.360
Oh, nothing.

01:02:01.400 --> 01:02:03.120
What do you mean, nothing?

01:02:04.840 --> 01:02:08.920
You think it makes me look fat,
it makes my ass look fat.

01:02:08.960 --> 01:02:10.520
Did I say that?

01:02:10.560 --> 01:02:13.920
- You think I've got a fat ass.
- You said that. I didn't.

01:02:13.960 --> 01:02:16.320
So you do think
I've got a fat ass.

01:02:16.360 --> 01:02:18.000
Give me a break.

01:02:18.040 --> 01:02:20.840
You wouldn't have said that
once upon a time.

01:02:20.880 --> 01:02:22.120
You liked my ass.

01:02:22.160 --> 01:02:26.160
I still like your ass.
I'm crazy about your ass.

01:02:26.200 --> 01:02:27.720
You don't love me anymore.

01:02:27.760 --> 01:02:29.720
Wear what you fucking want.

01:02:29.760 --> 01:02:32.560
Wear a fucking bathrobe,
for all I care.

01:02:40.200 --> 01:02:43.080
The trouble is, publishing
isn't what it used to be.

01:02:43.120 --> 01:02:44.960
It's the bottom line
that counts now...

01:02:45.000 --> 01:02:47.680
proven track records,
advance sales.

01:02:47.720 --> 01:02:48.840
No one's gonna invest
in a newcomer...

01:02:48.880 --> 01:02:50.040
who hasn't proven himself.

01:02:50.080 --> 01:02:53.000
So an unknown can't get
published unless he's known.

01:02:53.040 --> 01:02:54.760
Sounds like a Catch-22 to me.

01:02:54.760 --> 01:02:56.520
You could call it that.

01:02:56.560 --> 01:02:58.600
And your Parisian settings
don't help any.

01:02:58.640 --> 01:03:00.000
When are you
going to come back home...

01:03:00.040 --> 01:03:01.440
back to the United States,
where it's at?

01:03:01.480 --> 01:03:02.880
No, he wouldn't do that.

01:03:02.920 --> 01:03:05.440
Oscar's a fixture here.
He's like the Eiffel Tower.

01:03:05.480 --> 01:03:07.640
He's right, Beverly.
I love it here.

01:03:07.680 --> 01:03:10.000
- I feel at home.
- Good for you.

01:03:10.040 --> 01:03:12.960
Come on, get a life.
Paris is out. Vieux jeu.

01:03:13.000 --> 01:03:14.360
It's a literary mausoleum.

01:03:14.400 --> 01:03:17.320
Henry Miller
used it up fifty years ago.

01:03:17.360 --> 01:03:18.840
God, I don't think France
hasn't been the same...

01:03:18.880 --> 01:03:21.120
since they gave up absinthe.

01:03:22.800 --> 01:03:25.440
It's all right.
I'll be fine. Thank you.

01:03:25.480 --> 01:03:27.560
I'm fine. I'm fine.

01:03:29.680 --> 01:03:33.520
You know what?
I should make you my agent.

01:03:33.560 --> 01:03:35.520
That would solve
all my problems.

01:03:35.560 --> 01:03:37.600
"Paris is out. Vieux jeu."

01:03:37.640 --> 01:03:40.760
You really did me
some good tonight...

01:03:40.800 --> 01:03:42.720
like I don't have enough trouble
getting published.

01:03:42.760 --> 01:03:44.800
I couldn't bear to see you
crawl up her ass like that.

01:03:44.840 --> 01:03:47.320
I'll crawl up the ass of anyone
I fucking well feel like.

01:03:47.360 --> 01:03:48.800
Yours isn't the only one
in town.

01:03:48.840 --> 01:03:50.920
Is that how you feel?

01:03:50.960 --> 01:03:52.320
That's exactly how I feel.

01:03:52.360 --> 01:03:54.240
In that case, I'd better go.

01:03:54.280 --> 01:03:55.840
OK. You do that.

01:04:29.440 --> 01:04:30.760
I'm going now.

01:04:33.560 --> 01:04:35.160
Are you sad I'm going?

01:04:37.960 --> 01:04:39.080
You're not sad.

01:04:40.600 --> 01:04:43.840
I am sad,
but it's better this way.

01:05:04.280 --> 01:05:05.760
My keys.

01:05:05.800 --> 01:05:06.920
Thanks.

01:05:10.600 --> 01:05:12.560
I love you.
I love you so much.

01:05:12.600 --> 01:05:15.640
Please don't make me go.

01:05:20.840 --> 01:05:22.280
Stop crying.

01:05:24.520 --> 01:05:26.600
Go make some coffee
or something, huh?

01:05:56.800 --> 01:05:59.400
I came to dread bedtime.

01:06:02.080 --> 01:06:04.120
I would feel this...

01:06:04.160 --> 01:06:07.080
overpowering desire to sleep.

01:06:09.800 --> 01:06:11.240
I'm bushed.

01:06:20.800 --> 01:06:22.680
I'd feel sorry for her...

01:06:22.720 --> 01:06:24.120
Good night.

01:06:24.160 --> 01:06:27.160
...lying there with her belly
crying, "Famine..."

01:06:27.200 --> 01:06:29.600
her organs in turmoil.

01:06:29.680 --> 01:06:31.240
Kiss me good night.

01:06:39.080 --> 01:06:41.760
Not like that. Hold me.

01:06:41.800 --> 01:06:43.800
I would crush my lips
against hers...

01:06:43.840 --> 01:06:47.160
like you mash out a butt
in an ashtray...

01:06:47.200 --> 01:06:48.680
but that was only a prelude...

01:06:48.720 --> 01:06:51.640
to the most unoriginal act
known to man...

01:06:51.680 --> 01:06:54.920
the process referred to
as copulation.

01:07:02.240 --> 01:07:05.280
I felt like a rat in a trap.

01:07:05.320 --> 01:07:08.040
Out there,
people were having fun...

01:07:08.080 --> 01:07:10.960
dancing, making love.

01:07:11.000 --> 01:07:14.000
Paris was throbbing
to its own frenetic rhythms.

01:07:14.040 --> 01:07:17.160
They pounded away in my head,
driving me crazy.

01:07:18.520 --> 01:07:19.880
I craved variety.

01:07:19.920 --> 01:07:23.120
I hungered for noise
and excitement.

01:08:12.560 --> 01:08:14.120
Holy shit!

01:08:22.160 --> 01:08:24.520
Do you have to drink it
that way?

01:08:24.560 --> 01:08:26.760
Why can't you use a glass?

01:08:26.800 --> 01:08:29.160
What's the difference?
It tastes the same.

01:08:29.200 --> 01:08:31.080
It doesn't look the same.

01:08:31.120 --> 01:08:33.640
Oh-la-la. I didn't know
you were so delicate.

01:08:33.680 --> 01:08:36.160
- What do you mean, delicate?
- I mean delicate.

01:08:36.200 --> 01:08:37.279
I know what you mean...

01:08:37.319 --> 01:08:38.920
but it's just not
the right word in English.

01:08:38.960 --> 01:08:41.160
If you don't know the right word
in English, say it in French.

01:08:41.160 --> 01:08:44.040
I don't say it in French because
your French isn't good enough.

01:08:44.040 --> 01:08:46.240
It's better than your English.

01:08:46.279 --> 01:08:50.040
After all these years in Paris,
so it should be.

01:08:50.080 --> 01:08:52.399
Maybe your English
isn't that good, either.

01:08:52.439 --> 01:08:55.840
Maybe that's why no one wants
to publish your books.

01:08:55.880 --> 01:08:57.800
So now you're a literary critic?

01:08:57.800 --> 01:08:59.640
That's great
coming from a waitress.

01:08:59.680 --> 01:09:02.279
I'm not a waitress.
I'm a dancer.

01:09:02.319 --> 01:09:04.640
Dancer, hell.
You'd still be begging tips...

01:09:04.680 --> 01:09:07.520
if I hadn't picked you up
out of that fucking restaurant.

01:09:14.520 --> 01:09:17.160
You little bitch!

01:09:22.760 --> 01:09:24.439
OK, show's over.

01:09:24.479 --> 01:09:26.399
You can get up now.

01:09:42.600 --> 01:09:44.840
Jesus, don't do this to me.

01:09:44.880 --> 01:09:45.960
Baby?

01:09:46.000 --> 01:09:47.359
Come on, say something.

01:09:47.399 --> 01:09:48.479
Please.

01:09:53.720 --> 01:09:55.160
God Almighty.

01:10:14.160 --> 01:10:15.600
Sos médecin. Bonjour.

01:10:15.640 --> 01:10:18.960
Ma femme, elle est évanouie
soudainement.

01:10:19.000 --> 01:10:20.400
Dans quelles circonstances?

01:10:20.440 --> 01:10:23.680
Elle est tombée. Tombée.

01:10:23.720 --> 01:10:25.840
Sa tete a heurte un meuble.

01:10:25.880 --> 01:10:28.080
Saigne-t-elle due nez
ou des oreilles?

01:10:30.320 --> 01:10:32.320
Est-ce qu'elle prend
des médicaments?

01:10:33.040 --> 01:10:34.560
Quel age a-t-elle?

01:10:42.240 --> 01:10:43.960
- J'ai mal.
- Where?

01:10:46.760 --> 01:10:48.200
Ou tu as mal?

01:10:50.120 --> 01:10:51.560
My head.

01:10:51.560 --> 01:10:53.360
Is it bad?

01:10:54.400 --> 01:10:56.320
How bad is it?

01:10:56.360 --> 01:10:58.080
Tiger.

01:10:59.680 --> 01:11:02.960
- Should I call a doctor?
- No. Just hold me.

01:11:08.840 --> 01:11:11.000
Baby, forgive me, please.

01:11:11.040 --> 01:11:13.840
I love you.

01:11:24.520 --> 01:11:27.160
Wow. It's great!

01:11:27.200 --> 01:11:30.560
Thank you. Thank you.
I'm so happy.

01:11:46.680 --> 01:11:48.160
What a lovely evening.

01:11:48.200 --> 01:11:50.560
I wish it would last forever.

01:11:50.600 --> 01:11:53.040
Forever's a long time, baby.

01:11:54.280 --> 01:11:56.280
I can't think in those terms.

01:11:56.320 --> 01:11:57.400
I never could.

01:11:57.440 --> 01:11:59.320
But when something is good...

01:11:59.360 --> 01:12:01.720
don't you want it
to last forever?

01:12:01.760 --> 01:12:05.320
Sure, but good things never do.

01:12:05.320 --> 01:12:06.760
Not even us?

01:12:08.480 --> 01:12:11.000
Are we so good?

01:12:11.040 --> 01:12:12.200
Aren't we?

01:12:13.280 --> 01:12:16.880
Well, now that you
come to mention it, no.

01:12:16.920 --> 01:12:18.400
Not anymore.

01:12:21.440 --> 01:12:23.640
I...

01:12:23.680 --> 01:12:27.720
Come on, Mimi,
let's stop kidding ourselves.

01:12:27.720 --> 01:12:29.800
I don't understand.

01:12:29.840 --> 01:12:33.000
Look,
it was sweet while it lasted.

01:12:33.000 --> 01:12:37.480
Boy, it was sweet,
but it's going sour, isn't it?

01:12:39.040 --> 01:12:40.400
Well, isn't it?

01:12:42.240 --> 01:12:45.000
I'd been hoping that you'd
take the initiative...

01:12:45.040 --> 01:12:48.680
but, no, you seem quite happy
to let things drag on this way.

01:12:48.720 --> 01:12:50.040
Well, I'm not.

01:12:50.080 --> 01:12:52.200
I'm degrading myself
by degrading you.

01:12:52.240 --> 01:12:54.680
We're degrading each other,
for God's sake.

01:12:56.640 --> 01:12:59.040
Let's not spoil
a beautiful memory.

01:12:59.080 --> 01:13:02.480
Let's quit while we still have
a few shreds of dignity left.

01:13:04.560 --> 01:13:07.800
But I love you.
All I want is you.

01:13:07.840 --> 01:13:11.560
I want to marry you.
I want to give you babies.

01:13:11.600 --> 01:13:13.640
I want to give you
the rest of my life.

01:13:13.680 --> 01:13:16.160
I don't want the rest
of your life. I want my own.

01:13:16.200 --> 01:13:17.600
Can't you get it
through your head?

01:13:19.720 --> 01:13:21.640
What did I do wrong?

01:13:21.680 --> 01:13:23.600
Did I ever harm you?

01:13:25.360 --> 01:13:27.080
Oscar, tell me.

01:13:28.280 --> 01:13:31.200
Even a criminal
is told his crime.

01:13:31.240 --> 01:13:32.520
What did I do?

01:13:37.000 --> 01:13:39.040
You didn't do anything.

01:13:39.080 --> 01:13:40.160
You exist.

01:13:40.200 --> 01:13:41.360
That's all.

01:13:53.600 --> 01:13:54.720
I understand.

01:14:12.280 --> 01:14:14.400
Did I miss her?

01:14:14.440 --> 01:14:16.400
Sure, I did...

01:14:16.440 --> 01:14:20.560
but I also experienced
an incredible sense of freedom.

01:14:20.600 --> 01:14:22.960
The future seemed bright
with promise...

01:14:23.000 --> 01:14:27.040
peopled with a thousand
alluring images...

01:14:27.080 --> 01:14:28.840
most of them female.

01:14:34.240 --> 01:14:35.600
Oh, shit.

01:14:43.240 --> 01:14:44.400
It's me.

01:14:47.160 --> 01:14:49.040
I'm here.

01:14:49.080 --> 01:14:50.160
I'm scared.

01:14:50.200 --> 01:14:51.280
What?

01:14:51.320 --> 01:14:53.040
I can't live without you.

01:14:53.080 --> 01:14:54.960
I'm afraid
you're just gonna have to.

01:14:55.000 --> 01:14:56.080
I won't.

01:14:57.360 --> 01:14:59.720
We've been through this before,
haven't we?

01:14:59.760 --> 01:15:02.280
So why don't we give it a rest?

01:15:02.320 --> 01:15:05.520
Look up some friends.
Have some fun.

01:15:05.560 --> 01:15:07.760
We just went over the top,
that's all.

01:15:07.800 --> 01:15:09.040
In a few days...

01:15:09.080 --> 01:15:12.640
you'll be grateful to me
for having made the first move.

01:15:20.280 --> 01:15:22.200
Was she play-acting?

01:15:22.240 --> 01:15:23.480
I couldn't be sure.

01:15:23.520 --> 01:15:25.760
I called her old roommate.

01:15:25.800 --> 01:15:27.600
No dice.

01:15:27.640 --> 01:15:29.800
I spent the rest of the day
wondering...

01:15:29.840 --> 01:15:32.080
and half the night drinking.

01:15:52.600 --> 01:15:54.200
I was waiting for you.

01:15:54.240 --> 01:15:56.600
I can see that. I wonder why.

01:15:56.640 --> 01:15:57.720
You know why.

01:15:57.760 --> 01:15:59.840
I know I'm wrecked
and I'm gonna crash.

01:15:59.880 --> 01:16:02.240
- No. Wait.
- Let go of me.

01:16:02.280 --> 01:16:04.440
I want to tell you something.

01:16:04.480 --> 01:16:05.920
There's nothing more to be said.

01:16:05.960 --> 01:16:07.000
- Please!

01:16:07.040 --> 01:16:08.320
It's not going to make it
any easier on you.

01:16:08.360 --> 01:16:11.200
You've got to listen to me.
Please. Please listen to me.

